$interpreted: Rune: No...Elio...
Sanchez: Oh! Is that Rune!?
Rune: Sanchez...? Working...?
Sanchez: That's right~ Even though after winning at the Colosseum nobody asks about my criminal past, everybody is still pointing their fingers at me.
Rune: So for that reason, I plan on saving up some money for travel, then leaving the Desert and going somewhere else to make it big.
Sanchez: Just thinking about it makes me feel so excited about the future!
Rune: Sanchez is...excited about the future. Me too...
Sanchez: Let's go together! Following your old supervisor, that's the way to go!
Sanchez: In the Desert, to be a slave accused of killing their master is something you'll never throw off!
Rune: I can't leave...now. First, I must help Sophie...find Elio.
Sanchez: ......
Rune: Sanchez...what's wrong?
Sanchez: What's wrong with me? What's wrong with YOU? You're that worried about Sophie~ I didn't know she was your type!
Rune: Like...? What's that?
Sanchez: If you like, you love! Love, love, love~ If you don't like her, why would you help her do so much?
Sanchez: How about I teach you some moves?
Sanchez: Now that we're talking about it, you know what my old nickname was? Woman Crusher Sanchez── I ain't no joke!
Sanchez: How many women threw themselves at me ~~
Sanchez: Huh? Pretty woman...
Sanchez: Ouch!!! Ah!!!!
Miranda: Got you, you little thief! Gimme back my travel expenses!
Sanchez: Wait a second, I didn't take anything!
Miranda: Only this boat crew has moved my luggage. If it wasn't you then who was it!?
Sanchez: I didn't do anything! Help me, Rune!
Rune: Don't...bully...Sanchez!!
Sanchez: You've got such a pretty face, but such a bumbling mouth. I already told you it wasn't me. Do you not speak English?
Miranda: Oh, you say so and I'm supposed to believe you? Who knows if you're not lying to my face!
Rune: Good...point.
Sanchez: ...Hey! Bros before...woman. Shut it!
Miranda: Hmph. Even your friend said I make sense. You still want to argue?
Sanchez: Blast! Well, let's take this before someone else and do this face to face!
Miranda: Fine! We'll see who's scared of who!
